The paper discusses the development of a new type of Memory-Augmented Neural Network (MANN) that uses a structured memory to represent and manipulate graph-structured data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
